@baseUrl = http://localhost:5278
@usersEndpoint = /users

### ✅ GET all users
GET {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 🔍 GET user by valid ID
GET {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/1
Accept: application/json

###

### ❌ GET user by invalid ID
GET {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/999
Accept: application/json

###

### 🆕 POST valid user
POST {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

###

### ❌ POST invalid user (missing name)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid@example.com"
}

###

### ✏️ PUT valid update
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Updated",
  "email": "alice.updated@example.com"
}

###

### ❌ PUT invalid update (bad email)
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

###

### ❌ PUT non-existent user
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost",
  "email": "ghost@example.com"
}

###

### 🗑️ DELETE existing user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/1
Accept: application/json

###

### ❌ DELETE non-existent user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}{{usersEndpoint}}/999
Accept: application/json
